Fearmonger					KEY:Antipaladin Archetype ~ Fearmonger		CATEGORY:Archetype		TYPE:Archetype.AntipaladinArchetype																																		PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=1	PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Archetype,Antipaladin Archetype ~ Fearmonger],[!PREFACT:1,ABILITIES,Antipaladin_Archetype_TouchOfCorruption=True,Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty3=True,Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty6=True,Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty9=True,Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty12=True]																																				DESC:The fearmonger wants to do more than cause pain, misery, and confusion. He wishes to spread fear among his foes and infect entire populations with it.																																																																																																																																																																																																				ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Fearmonger ~ Feed on Fear|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=2	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Fearmonger ~ Frightening Cruelty|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=3																																																																																																																																																																																				COST:0	SOURCEPAGE:p.20																																																																																																																																																																																															FACT:Antipaladin_Archetype_TouchOfCorruption|true	FACT:Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty3|true	FACT:Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty6|true	FACT:Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty9|true	FACT:Antipaladin_Archetype_Cruelty12|true	FACT:Antipaladin_CF_TouchOfCorruption|true	FACT:Antipaladin_CF_Cruelty3|true	FACT:Antipaladin_CF_Cruelty6|true	FACT:Antipaladin_CF_Cruelty9|true	FACT:Antipaladin_CF_Cruelty12|true

Feed on Fear				KEY:Fearmonger ~ Feed on Fear				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.FearmongerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																																			DESC:The first time in a round a creature fails a saving throw against a fear effect created by a fearmonger's spell, spell-like ability, or supernatural ability (including any ability that causes a creature to be shaken, frightened, or panicked), the fearmonger is healed of %1 points of damage. If the fearmonger is at full hit points when this ability is activated, he instead gains an equal number of temporary hit points. These temporary hit points last for 1 minute. Temporary hit points gained through multiple successful uses of this ability do not stack; the duration increases instead. The antipaladin can use this ability %2 times per day.|AntipaladinLVL/2|CHA+AntipaladinLVL/2																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.20
Frightening Cruelty			KEY:Fearmonger ~ Frightening Cruelty		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Antipaladin Class Features.FearmongerClassFeatures.SpecialQuality.Supernatural																																																																																																																			DESC:The fearmonger must select shaken as his 3rd-level cruelty, dazed as his 6th-level cruelty, and frightened as his 9th-level cruelty. At 12th level, the fearmonger gains the panicked cruelty.																																																																																																																																																																																													ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Cruelty ~ Shaken|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=3	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Cruelty ~ Dazed|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=6	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Cruelty ~ Frightened|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=9	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Cruelty ~ Panicked|PRECLASS:1,Antipaladin=12																																																																																																																																																															SOURCEPAGE:p.20

